id: pm-hpjd
title: "CI: combine pnpm test + pnpm test:coverage into single coverage run"
description: "ci.yml runs `pnpm test` (PM_RUN_TESTS_SKIP_BUILD=1) on all 5 matrix entries and then `pnpm test:coverage` again on ubuntu/20. The coverage run executes all tests too, so ubuntu/20 runs the full suite twice (~6min wasted/run). Make ubuntu/20 use `pnpm test:coverage` only; keep `pnpm test` only for the other matrix entries."
type: Issue
status: closed
priority: 1
tags[4]: ci,duplication,performance,pm-cli
created_at: "2026-05-16T22:07:35.770Z"
updated_at: "2026-05-16T23:13:08.454Z"
author: maintainer-agent
acceptance_criteria: ubuntu-latest+node20 runs tests exactly once via coverage path; other matrix entries run pnpm test as before; CI overall time reduced by ~3min on ubuntu/20 entry.
parent: pm-tzwy
resolution: Fixed by skipping duplicate plain test on the ubuntu-latest Node 20 coverage leg.
expected_result: "Ubuntu Node 20 runs the full suite once via coverage, while other matrix entries still run pnpm test."
actual_result: "ci.yml guard and workflow contract regression are in place; linked test, coverage, release gate, and Sentry/telemetry gate passed."
comments[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-05-16T23:12:21.853Z",codex-agent,"Evidence: .github/workflows/ci.yml now skips plain pnpm test only on ubuntu-latest Node 20, where pnpm test:coverage still runs the full test suite once. CI workflow contract asserts the guard. Linked test, full coverage, release gate, and required Sentry/telemetry gate passed."
